---
# AstrOs.ESP C/C++ formatting rules.
# Based on LLVM defaults with overrides chosen to match the existing codebase,
# which uses Allman brace style, 4-space indent, and a 120-column limit.
#
# Phase 1 laid down this file; Phase 2 calibrated it against the actual
# codebase and ran a full-repo reformat to establish a clean baseline.
#
# Overrides (relative to LLVM defaults):
#   IndentWidth: 4               — matches existing code
#   ColumnLimit: 120             — fits two panes side-by-side on a typical monitor
#   PointerAlignment: Right      — matches the `char *foo` / `uint8_t *data` convention
#   BreakBeforeBraces: Allman    — brace-on-next-line throughout the codebase
#   AllowShortFunctionsOnASingleLine: Empty  — collapse empty bodies: `Foo() {}`
#   AccessModifierOffset: -4     — `public:`/`private:` at column 0 inside classes
#   NamespaceIndentation: All    — indent inside namespace blocks
BasedOnStyle: LLVM
IndentWidth: 4
ColumnLimit: 120
PointerAlignment: Right
BreakBeforeBraces: Allman
AllowShortFunctionsOnASingleLine: Empty
AccessModifierOffset: -4
NamespaceIndentation: All
---
